In 2009, Christie traveled to India with a longtime customer to participate in a volunteer project. The Atlanta tea shop owner decided to continue on alone to the Darjeeling region of northeast India to explore the tea plantations. In her time there, Christie encountered a group of young girls who were being forced out of their orphanage for exceeding the age of sixteen. With no families to return to, Christie knew the girls would likely face grim futures in poverty and exploitation.
